node.title: College Football Playoff Rankings Released 11/30/2021: Georgia Still No. 1
node.alt: Robert Beal Jr. #33 of the Georgia Bulldogs reacts after a play against the Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets during the first quarter at Bobby Dodd Stadium on November 27, 2021 in Atlanta, Georgia.
node.description: The Cincinnati Bearcats remain in the top 4 for a playoff spot with one weekend of regular season to go.
node.content:
["The College Football Playoff committee released its next-to-last rankings for the 2021 season, and Georgia remains the top dog leading the pack. Following conference championships this weekend, the committee will release its final rankings at noon Sunday. At that point, the playoff will be set and teams will know where they'll play bowl games.", "In no surprise Tuesday night, Georgia is still the No. 1 team. The Bulldogs will play the Southeastern Conference (SEC) championship this Saturday against Alabama, which is No. 3 in the latest rankings.", "", "
Robert Beal Jr. #33 of the Georgia Bulldogs reacts after a play against the Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets during the first quarter at Bobby Dodd Stadium on November 27, 2021 in Atlanta, Georgia.
", "Michigan vaulted to No. 2 after its convincing win last Saturday over Ohio State, which fell from the second spot to No. 7. Michigan will play No. 13 Iowa for the Big Ten championship this Saturday.", "Cincinnati remains in the playoff mix as the Bearcats are No. 4, just ahead of Oklahoma State at No. 5. Cincinnati will play No. 21 Houston for the American Athletic Conference (AAC) title this weekend while Oklahoma State will face No. 9 Baylor for the Big 12 championship.", "Here are the rankings released Tuesday night:", "If the playoffs began with these rankings, the semifinals would be like this:", "Georgia vs Cincinnati (Orange Bowl)\nMichigan vs Alabama (Cotton Bowl)", "This is a developing story."]
